DAY 1 - started learning about the swing and its various methods and got to know about basics of 2-D game development using Java.
        Used Swing to create a Window class and game panel class.
        Implemented JFrame and its size methods to create a window, exit button and configure its characterstics.
        Game panel class extends Jpanel to inherit additional features. Coded Screen settings such as pixels for character and the size of the window itself. 
        class Gamepanel implements Runnable to create a thread called gameThread. This Game thread is essential as a 2-d game has an important concept of time. Even if the character stays still the world around him still moves and runs. this is done by a thread class and 
        a run method which makes the thread run until != null.
